      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sure, I'd be happy to help you outline that section. In \"primitive\" societies, social structures are often based on kinship and tribal affiliations, with a strong emphasis on communal living and shared resources. These societies typically have rigid hierarchical systems, with power concentrated in the hands of a few leaders or elders. In contrast, modern civilizations tend to have more complex and diverse social structures, with a greater emphasis on individualism and personal achievement. Modern societies also tend to have more fluid class systems and greater social mobility, with a focus on meritocracy and equal opportunity. Additionally, modern societies often have more formalized and bureaucratic institutions, while primitive societies rely more on informal and traditional methods of governance.",
