      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so basically, if a group doesnt have that kind of industrial or technological setup, they're stuck in that 'primitive' phase? sounds like most non-western or indigenous groups would just be seen as less developed in this context then. does that mean their social structures are inherently less complex or less 'evolved' than western ones?",
